summary: “the golden rays of sunshine make your eyes as blue as the ocean i’m holding you in” chris evans x reader
title: “the golden rays of sunshine make your eyes as blue as the ocean i’m holding you in” chris evans x reader
body:
“the golden rays of sunshine make your eyes as blue as the ocean i’m holding you in” chris evans x damsel

word count: 620 (its abt quality not quantity k)

warnings: fluff!

also, listen to drive by halsey while reading this ;)

summary: “i thought working twelve hours a day was supposed to be exhausting me. why do i wanna get out of this bed and drive to the ocean?” you and chris had been on set from 8 am to 8 pm and yet you had a lot of energy left to spend. good thing the ocean was only an hour-long drive away.

“i have just the perfect song for this,” you said and opened your mobile phone, looking for a particular song. you were wearing a long, oversized, worn-out shirt and shorts, and chris was sitting next to you in the no-roof car, with his favorite plain white shirt and gray sweatpants.

my hands wrapped around your stick shift, swerving on the 405, i can never keep my eyes off this

“we’ll be there during golden hour, can it get any better?” you smiled and stretched your arms, falling for the view and happening, the way your life seemed to be in that exact moment. it felt like the rarest but most beautiful it could be.

“we got the mixed alcohol, the weather is perfect, i can see the moon and the sun, and i have you.” you added and caressed his neck and jaw softly with your fingers, trying not to distract him but you just couldn’t help yourself.

my neck, the feeling of your soft lips. illuminated in the light, bouncing off the exit signs i missed

you sang along to the words of the song, chris enjoying the sound of you being happy and relaxed. you weren’t like this enough, he loved seeing you like this, he’d give up everything if it meant for you to always feel like this.

“hey,” he took your hand and smiled overly fondly at you, “i love you so much.”

you drove for nearly an hour more until you arrived at the beach, fortunately being the only one there. you took your bag out of the car and held chris’ hand as you walked away from the car.

“don’t wanna be drunk, i’ve got the feeling i’ll want to remember tonight. however…” you grinned at chris and he smiled down and pulled you closer to him, not knowing how to handle his affection to your happiness quite well. so he kissed you.

you pulled away and tried fighting the smile that’d been glued on your face for the entirety of the night so far. you took the bottle of vodka and poured a good amount of it into a can of cola. balancing the ratio to perfection, and drinking half of it. you handed chris the rest of it. knowing he’s kind of sensitive to alcohol you made sure to only give him a fourth of all of it.

after emptying the can he pulled you into a kiss again, tasting the alcohol on your lips.

“i love you.” you said between breaths and smiled at him.

“i love you.” he responded.

for a moment you stood there and looked. enjoying he feeling of each other’s touch, the affection and infatuation surrounding and embodying the two of you.

it was only until chris took of his shirt and pants that you giggled and did the same, leaving yourself in nothing but your black underwear.

“c’mere,” he said and pulled you off the ground, taking you into the surprisingly warm water. your laughter overpowering the sounds of the waves for a while, having you completely forget that the rest of the world is still there.

he let go of you, but you not of him.

“hold on to me.” you whispered and moved closer. he took you by your waist and looked you in your shiny eyes. taking you back in his arms, holding you close to him, you stared back into his eyes.

“the golden rays of sunshine make your eyes as blue as the ocean i’m holding you in.” he said softly and under his breath, cupping your cheeks and trailing his lips from your jaw to your neck.

“may have said this too many times already,” you whispered, “but i really love you so much.”

“you can never say it enough. i love you too. i love seeing you like this.”
